1. the client handles user input, then based on that input makes HTTP requests to the server. The server then
then communicates with the database to generate responses and send the data back to the client so that it
can render the response data.

2.The rise in Nodes popularity is due to its use of "Isomorphic Javascript", which means that 
you can use javascript to write code on both the client and the server, making it much easier to 
write code for the two. Examples of companies that use Node.js are Paypal, LinkedIn, and Walmart.

